  "body": "<!-- Before filling this issue, please read the Wiki (https://github.com/fossology/fossology/wiki)\r\nand search if the bug do not already exists in the issues (https://github.com/fossology/fossology/issues). -->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nHello,\r\n\r\nI am trying to integrate a fossology instance with my project workflow.\r\n\r\nWhat i want to do is make the task easier for the users of my app, and get the results of the fossology scan from their SRC RPM files without even going to the foss UI.\r\n\r\nThe question is, is there a way to create different users through Rest API calls in fossology ? (not using the admin foss web ui).\r\n\r\nI guess i will have to copy/create lots of information in my personal database, and take in consideration all the relationships with groups/users/permission/roles/licences, etc), which seems to me pretty big!\r\n\r\nThanks for your answers!",
